Applications:
The system is used to bond together 2 wafers, previously aligned using the aligner (with max precision of +/- 5 µm). 
Available bonding processes:
Anodic bonding: between silicon and Borofloat-33 (tailor made pirex);
Fusion (thermo-compressive) bonding: between Si and Si or Fused Silica and Fused Silica; all the substrates must be electronic grade and CMOS compatible,  highly planarity of bonded surfaces is required. The process requires a final annealing at 1000°C;
Glue bonding: between wafers of different materials; the glue used is SU-8 3000, an epoxy patternable photoresist with 10 µm thickness

